</p>
<p><b>Human Rights Council 
Twenty-eighth session</b> 
</p>
<p>Agenda item 3 
</p>
<p><b>Promotion and protection of all human rights, 
</b></p>
<p><b>civil, political, economic, social and cultural rights, 
</b></p>
<p><b>including the right to development 
</b></p>
<p><b>  Report of the Special Rapporteur on the promotion and  
  protection of human rights and fundamental freedoms while 
  countering terrorism, Ben Emmerson</b>*<b> 
</b></p>
<p><b>  Note by the Secretariat 
</b></p>
<p>In its resolution 25/7, the Human Rights Council requested the Special Rapporteur 
</p>
<p>on the promotion and protection of human rights and fundamental freedoms while 
</p>
<p>countering terrorism to report regularly to the Council and to present his reports, bearing in 
</p>
<p>mind the content of that resolution, in conformity with its annual programme of work. The 
</p>
<p>Special Rapporteur was due to submit his annual report to the Council at its twenty-eighth 
</p>
<p>session (A/HRC/28/67). 
</p>
<p>At the request of the mandate holder, the Special Rapporteur will submit his annual 
</p>
<p>report to the Council for its consideration at its twenty-ninth session. 
</p>
<p>    
</p>
<p>  
</p>
<p> * Late submission. 
</p>
